WEBVTT

00:00:00.910 --> 00:00:09.089
It is my great pleasure to warmly welcome all of you and to say, Shalom.

00:00:09.089 --> 00:00:11.650
Why is saying that appropriate?

00:00:11.650 --> 00:00:17.350
Well Shalom is the Hebrew word for peace, and it occurs over two hundred times in the

00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:18.670
Bible.

00:00:18.670 --> 00:00:25.969
When its use is a greeting, just as I used it, it means, may you have peace.

00:00:25.969 --> 00:00:31.570
So what could be a more appropriate way to greet all of you at the start of this pursue

00:00:31.570 --> 00:00:36.450
peace, convention of Jehovah's Witnesses?

00:00:36.450 --> 00:00:42.810
We are very pleased that you're with us, and we assure you you will not be disappointed.

00:00:42.810 --> 00:00:48.210
To the contrary, you'll be glad you were able to devote three days to learning what the

00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:56.490
Bible says about how to gain and maintain peace in all areas of your life.

00:00:56.490 --> 00:01:01.789
But now, let's begin by talking about the person who has drawn us all together for this

00:01:01.789 --> 00:01:10.090
convention, Jehovah, and how we delight in talking about our marvelous heavenly Father.

00:01:10.090 --> 00:01:14.530
Philippians 4.9 caused Jehovah the God of peace.

00:01:14.609 --> 00:01:21.489
Nice true, he possesses many qualities, love, justice, wisdom, power, but he also possesses

00:01:21.489 --> 00:01:23.890
the quality of peace.

00:01:23.890 --> 00:01:29.530
If you think about it, he is at peace with himself, at peace with angels, at peace with

00:01:29.530 --> 00:01:33.569
faithful humans, yes, he is the God of peace.

00:01:33.569 --> 00:01:38.890
But here's a question, does Jehovah keep this peace to himself?

00:01:38.890 --> 00:01:43.689
Well, let's get the answer, Romans chapter 15.

00:01:44.689 --> 00:01:50.290
And please, let's read verse number 33.

00:01:50.290 --> 00:01:57.569
May the God who gives peace be with all of you, amen.

00:01:57.569 --> 00:02:00.849
So he generously gives this peace as we'll be discussing.

00:02:00.849 --> 00:02:06.730
In fact, he gives every good gift, every perfect present according to James 117.

00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:10.770
And one of his finest presents is the gift of peace.

00:02:10.770 --> 00:02:15.449
And here's another question, what kind of peace does Jehovah give?

00:02:15.449 --> 00:02:21.770
Well, many equate peace with freedom from conflict and strife in one's life.

00:02:21.770 --> 00:02:25.370
But the peace Jehovah gives is a lot more than that.

00:02:25.370 --> 00:02:35.250
The peace that only Jehovah can supply brings in feelings of safety, security, well-being.

00:02:35.250 --> 00:02:40.129
This Jehovah-given peace is described very nicely in Philippians chapter 4.

00:02:40.129 --> 00:02:41.530
Let's go there.

00:02:41.530 --> 00:02:48.650
Philippians 4, beginning in verse 6, do not be anxious over anything, but in everything

00:02:48.650 --> 00:02:56.889
by prayer and supplication, along with thanksgiving, that your petitions be made known to God.

00:02:56.889 --> 00:03:04.969
And the peace of God that surpasses all understanding will guard your hearts and your mental powers

00:03:05.009 --> 00:03:07.370
by means of Christ Jesus.

00:03:07.370 --> 00:03:12.930
So notice, Jehovah is saying, do not be anxious over anything.

00:03:12.930 --> 00:03:17.370
Would Jehovah tell us to do something it was impossible for us to do?

00:03:17.370 --> 00:03:18.530
No.

00:03:18.530 --> 00:03:24.889
But obviously, he's talking about not being overly anxious.

00:03:24.889 --> 00:03:27.729
Controlled anxiety can actually be beneficial.

00:03:27.729 --> 00:03:30.969
It can move us to show concern for others.

00:03:30.969 --> 00:03:36.490
It can motivate us to work enthusiastically to accomplish an assignment.

00:03:36.490 --> 00:03:39.210
But now what about excessive uncontrolled anxiety?

00:03:39.210 --> 00:03:42.009
Well, I can lead to physical problems.

00:03:42.009 --> 00:03:46.849
Depression can be crippling, debilitating, infebling.

00:03:46.849 --> 00:03:54.370
But now, how can we avoid being overly anxious over anything?

00:03:54.370 --> 00:04:00.409
The answer is given in the next words of Philippians 4, 6, and 7, after telling us not

00:04:00.409 --> 00:04:03.650
to be anxious, Jehovah gives the antidote.

00:04:03.650 --> 00:04:10.889
He basically tells us to pray, supplicate, petition him, and we will get that peace of God.

00:04:10.889 --> 00:04:19.250
But now what does the Scripture mean when it says that this peace of God surpasses all

00:04:19.250 --> 00:04:20.569
understanding?

00:04:20.569 --> 00:04:26.730
Well, we could say that it's so amazing, so powerful, that we limited humans cannot

00:04:26.730 --> 00:04:28.810
fully understand it.

00:04:28.810 --> 00:04:32.529
It defies logic from a human standpoint.

00:04:32.529 --> 00:04:36.850
Our hearts and minds may be filled with so much worry, fear, anxiety.

00:04:36.850 --> 00:04:42.769
We see no way out, but we beg Jehovah for the peace that he can supply.

00:04:42.769 --> 00:04:44.370
And then what happens?

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:52.610
Our minds and hearts amazingly are filled with calmness, security, tranquility.

00:04:52.610 --> 00:04:58.889
Lorraine, a young girl whose mother was dying of cancer, said this.

00:04:58.889 --> 00:05:03.689
I was in the room when my mother took her last breath.

00:05:03.689 --> 00:05:08.970
I asked Jehovah to give me the strength to endure and to get through this.

00:05:08.970 --> 00:05:15.129
Immediately I felt the peace of God.

00:05:15.129 --> 00:05:21.850
But now what is meant by the expression, the peace of God will guard your hearts and

00:05:21.850 --> 00:05:22.850
your mental powers.

00:05:22.850 --> 00:05:29.689
Well, the Greek word translated guard is a military term that evokes a mental picture

00:05:29.689 --> 00:05:33.730
of soldiers maintaining a day and night watch.

00:05:33.730 --> 00:05:40.370
In the same way, see this peace of God can act like a 24 hour guard over our hearts and

00:05:40.370 --> 00:05:45.769
mental powers, keeping them calm, secure, and tranquil.

00:05:46.689 --> 00:05:53.930
Now here's a question, what is the key ingredient to are being able to receive this miraculous

00:05:53.930 --> 00:05:55.769
peace of God?

00:05:55.769 --> 00:06:01.490
The answer, having a close friendship with Jehovah.

00:06:01.490 --> 00:06:07.490
The Apostle Paul experienced firsthand many times that having inner peace depends not

00:06:07.490 --> 00:06:13.649
on circumstances, but rather on a close personal relationship with Jehovah.

00:06:13.730 --> 00:06:19.930
For example, on one occasion, because Paul and Silas boldly preached, they had their

00:06:19.930 --> 00:06:22.649
garments ripped off of them.

00:06:22.649 --> 00:06:25.649
They were beaten many blows with rods.

00:06:25.649 --> 00:06:28.129
They were thrown into the inner prison.

00:06:28.129 --> 00:06:31.250
Their feet were fastened in stocks.

00:06:31.250 --> 00:06:37.769
But in the middle of the night, what if Paul and Silas began to do, they began to pray,

00:06:37.769 --> 00:06:40.610
placing sawns of praise to Jehovah.

00:06:40.610 --> 00:06:45.930
In amazement, all the other prisoners were listening to them.

00:06:45.930 --> 00:06:52.449
So obviously, their very, very unfavorable circumstances had not robbed them of their

00:06:52.449 --> 00:06:54.529
precious peace of God.

00:06:54.529 --> 00:06:58.610
So let's learn this valuable lesson from Paul and Silas.

00:06:58.610 --> 00:07:05.009
Having the peace of God is not dependent on our circumstances, but it is dependent on

00:07:05.009 --> 00:07:10.449
having a close personal relationship with Jehovah.

00:07:10.449 --> 00:07:15.649
Thus far, we've discussed how Jehovah is a God of peace, who gives peace, and we've

00:07:15.649 --> 00:07:18.370
talked about what kind of peace he gives.

00:07:18.370 --> 00:07:24.290
But now we ask, to whom does Jehovah give peace?

00:07:24.290 --> 00:07:31.050
The simple answer is, Jehovah gives peace to those who draw close to him and want to

00:07:31.050 --> 00:07:33.490
follow his guidance.

00:07:33.490 --> 00:07:40.490
So receiving peace from Jehovah starts with living a clean life following Jehovah's

00:07:40.490 --> 00:07:42.769
righteous moral standards.

00:07:42.769 --> 00:07:50.089
Many people in Satan's world, as you know, believe that God will accept them as they are,

00:07:50.089 --> 00:07:53.730
that God in effect will lower his standard to accommodate them.

00:07:53.730 --> 00:07:56.089
Can you imagine such pride?

00:07:56.089 --> 00:08:03.449
That would be like a pot telling its maker, the potter, how the pot must be used.

00:08:03.490 --> 00:08:07.410
And the potter must accept this, whether he likes it or not.

00:08:07.410 --> 00:08:10.009
Well, we know it doesn't work that way, does it?

00:08:10.009 --> 00:08:13.089
We have to come up to Jehovah's righteous standards.

00:08:13.089 --> 00:08:18.649
Now he'll help us, but we do the changing, certainly not, Jehovah.

00:08:18.649 --> 00:08:26.970
Interestingly, James chapter 3, verse 17 says that the wisdom from above is first of

00:08:26.970 --> 00:08:31.730
all pure, then peaceable.

00:08:31.730 --> 00:08:38.129
So if we want peace from Jehovah that will result in peaceful lives, we must be pure according

00:08:38.129 --> 00:08:40.610
to Jehovah's moral standards.

